 in a region that has in the last four decades been transformed from a primarily agricultural economy to a primarily industrial one. Offering a new form of ethnography appropriate for the study of suprastate polities and a globalized economy, Immediate Struggles contributes to our understanding of one region as well as the way we think about changing class relations, modes of production, and cultural practices in a newly emerging Europe. The authors also consider how phenomena such as the "informal economy" and "black market" are not marginal to the normal operation of state and economic institutions but are intertwined with both.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEthnologyzSpainzBajo Segura. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aagriculture.  aalienation.  acultural practices.  aethnographers.  aethnography.  aeurope.  aglobal economy.  aglobalization.  agovernment and governing.  ahistorians.  ahistorical perspective.  aindustrial economy.  ainformal economy.  anonfiction.  aoral histories.  apolitical economies.  apolitical economy.  apower struggles.  aregional economies.  arural landscape.  asocial impact.  aspain.  aspanish culture.  aspanish politics.  aspanish society.  avega baja region.  aworking class.1 aSmith, Gavin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024569340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093901140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520939011423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520939011/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-all